==English==

===Etymology===
From {{etyl|fro}} ''[[neveu]]'' (modern ''neveu''), from {{etyl|la}} ''[[nepos]]''

===Pronunciation===
* {{a|RP}} {{IPA|/ˈnɛv.ju/}}, {{SAMPA|/nEvju/}} (''somewhat dated'') ''or'' {{IPA|/ˈnɛf.ju/}}, {{SAMPA|/nEfju/}}
* {{audio|en-us-nephew.ogg|Audio (US)}}

===Noun===
{{wikipedia}}
{{en-noun}}

# A son of one's [[sibling]]; either a [[son]] of one's [[brother]] ([[fraternal]] nephew) or a son of one's [[sister]] ([[sororal]] nephew).

